Uses of Interface
javaslang.collection.Seq

  • Packages that use Seq 
    Package Description
    javaslang.collection
    Immutable collections based on Traversable like the linked list List and the lazy linked list Stream.

    • Uses of Seq in javaslang.collection

      Subinterfaces of Seq in javaslang.collection 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  IndexedSeq<T>
      Interface for indexed sequences.
      interface  LinearSeq<T>
      Interface for linear sequences.
      interface  List<T>
      A List is an eager sequence of elements.
      interface  Stack<T>
      A Stack stores elements allowing a last-in-first-out (LIFO) retrieval.
      interface  Stream<T>
      A Stream is lazy sequence of elements which may be infinitely long.
